author: buffalonews
title: Kathy Hochul heads to Iowa to campaign for Hillary Clinton
text:
Lt. Gov. Kathleen C. Hochul will travel to Iowa Sunday to campaign for a long time political ally – Hillary Rodham Clinton.
The New York Daily News reported Friday that the former Hamburg congresswoman and Erie County clerk will appear at “Women for Hillary” events in Des Moines and Sioux City.
Hochul has long maintained close relations with the former New York senator and secretary of state. She also joins with Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo in supporting Clinton for president.
